mcp-bridge (2.0.0~rc1-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Rename: server-mcp-bridge -> mcp-bridge (Debian package), binary
    /usr/bin/server-mcp-bridge -> /usr/bin/mcp_bridge. Config moves
    from /etc/server-mcp-bridge/ to /etc/mcp_bridge/, state to
    /var/lib/mcp_bridge/, logs to /var/log/mcp_bridge/.
  * Daemon now runs as system user 'mcp' (formerly 'mcp-bridge').
  * No behavioural change in this release; the rename is the entire
    delta. Clients continue to use HTTP+JSON with the auto-generated
    bearer token. Subsequent 2.x releases will introduce native MCP
    (JSON-RPC 2.0) transport, multi-user auth, and a setuid helper
    for sudoers grant management.
  * Note: existing 1.x installations have no in-place upgrade path;
    run apt purge server-mcp-bridge before installing this package.

 -- TheParadox20 <noreply@example.com>  Sun, 03 May 2026 10:00:00 +0000

server-mcp-bridge (1.0.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Initial release.
  * 62 tools across 8 modules: files, database, networking, firewall,
    web server, processes, command execution, sandboxed code execution.
  * Cross-platform support (Linux and Windows).
  * Bearer token authentication with constant-time comparison.
  * Per-IP rate limiting, rotating log files, context tracking.
  * Sandbox isolation via bubblewrap, namespaces, or ulimit fallback.

